      <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_anti-cancer_drug_cycle">Anti-Cancer Drug Cycle</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_clinical_intervention">CLINICAL INTERVENTION</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_anti-cancer_drug_cycle">Anti-Cancer Drug Cycle</xref>
 is the period of time during which anti-cancer drugs are administered to a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 in an agreed pattern.        </p>
      <p>
A new 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_anti-cancer_drug_cycle">Anti-Cancer Drug Cycle</xref>
 commences when the original pattern starts again.        </p>
